  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/smartphones/\" rel=\"tag\">智能手机</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"cn.engadget.com/2014/01/30/lenovo-gets-motorola-but-google-gets-to-keep-its-skunkworks/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/adam/5072f38bf00059d28d8a6af769db764f/ara1blogpost.jpg\" style=\"width: 620px; height: 413px;\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n今早看过 Lenovo 买下 Motorola Mobility 的消息之后，有没有实时被吓醒了呢？虽然现在 Lenovo 基本上已经是 Moto 的新主人，但据报原来 Google 除了会保留 Moto 绝大多数专利的拥有权之外，还会将后者的高科技计划部门留为己用并将之纳入 Android 的团队当中。这个部门本来的职责是开发一些比较有未来感的东西，例如他们在 AllThingsD D11 大会上展示的<a href=\"http://allthingsd.com/20130603/passwords-on-your-skin-and-in-your-stomach-inside-googles-wild-motorola-research-projects-video/\">密码纹身</a>、身份认证药丸和相信是最为人所知的 <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/ProjectAra/\">Project Ara</a> 手机模块化计划；据指 Motorola 有可能在冬季里发放这个计划的开发者工具。所以各位对此很感兴趣的读者，理应不用怕其会因 Lenovo 收购 Moto 的消息而受影响呢。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/01/29/lenovo-gets-motorola-but-google-gets-to-keep-its-skunkworks/\">Engadget</a></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/30/lenovo-gets-motorola-but-google-gets-to-keep-its-skunkworks/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20819156/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/30/lenovo-gets-motorola-but-google-gets-to-keep-its-skunkworks/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
